Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this software and associated documentation files (the "Viss Programming Language", its compiler, package manager, and standard libraries), to deal in the Software without restriction, including without limitation the rights to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software, and to permit persons to whom the Software is furnished to do so, subject to the following conditions:

1. **The Right to Improve:** Everyone has the absolute right to modify Viss, compile custom versions, and build upon this project.
2. **Make It Better, Not Worse:** You must strive to make the language better, not worse. Keep the prefix-oriented design clean, fast, and beautiful. Every version that brings improvements and joy is highly appreciated.
3. **Absolute Freedom:** You are allowed to do whatever you want with this language and its tools. Create, experiment, build, and have fun!
4. **No Warranty:** The software is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind, express or implied.

Let the future of Viss be shaped by creativity, kindness, and collaboration! 🚀💙
